abstract: A listing of discussions, film screenings, cultural activities and walking tours in New York City.
snippet: A listing of discussions, film screenings, cultural activities and walking tours in New York City.
lead_paragraph: Talks on Hip-Hop (Thursday) Hip-hop may be one of the newer kids on the musical block, but its cultural impact runs as deep as any genre that has preceded it. It’s the focus of a slide show that will accompany a discussion with the photographer Jamel Shabazz and Wes Jackson, founder of Brooklyn Bodega, a branding and promotional company, at the Brooklyn Historical Society, 128 Pierrepont Street, Brooklyn Heights.
byline_original: By Anne Mancuso and Martin Tsai

abstract: A new survey finds 56 Democratic lawmakers on Capitol Hill already committing to support Hillary Rodham Clinton if she runs for president in 2016.
snippet: A new survey finds 56 Democratic lawmakers on Capitol Hill already committing to support Hillary Rodham Clinton if she runs for president in 2016.
lead_paragraph: On Monday, Hillary Rodham Clinton again said she had not yet decided whether she would run for president in 2016. That has not stopped the Democratic Party from coalescing around her.

abstract: Andy Warhol’s 1964 film “Empire” is seven hours of the Empire State Building doing nothing. What’s it like to watch the whole thing?
snippet: Andy Warhol’s 1964 film “Empire” is seven hours of the Empire State Building doing nothing. What’s it like to watch the whole thing?
lead_paragraph: ANDY WARHOL was a genius, but he could be mean. He loved to make his acolytes squabble. He’d torture visitors by blaring the same pop song over and over.
